      }
    ],
    "type" : "illegal_argument_exception",
    "reason" : "position overflowed Integer.MAX_VALUE (got posIncr=1 lastPosition=0 position=-1) for field 'tags._index_phrase'"
  },
  "status" : 400
}

```

**Steps to reproduce**:

1. Create an index with the following mapping
```
PUT test
{
  "mappings": {
    "properties": {
      "tags": {
        "index_phrases": true,
        "type": "text"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

2. Index a document
```
POST test/_doc
{
  "tags": [
    "bad",
    "Prio 1"
  ]
}
```

**Expected result:** The document is indexed.
**Actual Result:** Illegal argument exception.

I've tested the same steps on a 7.10 version of Elasticsearch and the document is indexed correctly.

Relates to https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch-net/issues/5399

