This issue is slightly different but somewhat related to #70271.

Composite aggs on a field that have the same name but different types in different indices can produce confusing errors. To reproduce:
```
DELETE index-*

POST index-a/_doc
{
  "val" : 1
}

POST index-b/_doc
{
  "val" : 1.0
}

POST index-*/_refresh

POST index-*/_search
{
  "size": 0,
  "aggregations": {
    "groupby": {
      "composite": {
        "sources": [
          {
            "agg": {
              "terms": {
                "field": "val"
              }
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  }
}
```
This example generates and error `class java.lang.Long cannot be cast to class java.lang.Double (java.lang.Long and java.lang.Double are in module java.base of loader 'bootstrap')`

